TITLE: First on CNN: 2 Americans held by the Taliban have been released, sources tell CNN
SUMMARY: Two Americans who had been detained by the Taliban in Afghanistan have been released and are en route to Qatar, three sources familiar with the matter tell CNN.

TITLE: US Postal Service fulfills top Biden climate goal with deployment of 66,000 electric delivery trucks
SUMMARY: The US Postal Service on Tuesday announced its intention to deploy at least 66,000 electric delivery trucks by 2028, satisfying a key goal for the Biden administration's climate agenda.

SUMMARY: New retirement rules could make it easier for Americans to accumulate retirement savings â€” and less costly to withdraw them, if lawmakers pass their end-of-year omnibus spending package.

TITLE: 6.4 magnitude earthquake shakes Northern California
SUMMARY: A 6.4 magnitude earthquake impacted Northern California's Eureka area early Tuesday, according to the US Geological Survey, leaving thousands without power. Follow the latest news here.

TITLE: Morgan Stanley warns US profits could drop like in 2008, tanking stocks
SUMMARY: One of Wall Street's top executives is worried about a repeat of 2008. At least, partially.

TITLE: Russia's war in Ukraine
SUMMARY: Russian President Vladimir Putin has admitted that the situation in four occupied Ukrainian territories is "extremely complicated," a window into the challenges facing Moscow as the war rages on. Follow live updates here.

TITLE: What should I do if my luggage is delayed, lost or damaged?
SUMMARY: The prospect of airlines losing luggage looms larger than ever. Here's what to do to help prevent your baggage from being delayed or lost -- and what to do if it's gone forever.

TITLE: UK lawmakers call on Sun newspaper to sanction Jeremy Clarkson over 'violent misogynist' Meghan article
SUMMARY: A group of British lawmakers are calling for action to be taken against columnist Jeremy Clarkson after he wrote a "violent misogynist" opinion piece about Meghan, the Duchess of Sussex in the Sun newspaper, which was later retracted.

TITLE: Biden administration gears up for end of Trump-era border restriction as Supreme Court considers whether to keep it in place
SUMMARY: The Biden administration is still bracing for the end of a Trump-era border restriction even after the chief justice of the Supreme Court temporarily paused the end of the program.

TITLE: The Masters will allow LIV golfers to compete in 2023 tournament
SUMMARY: Golfers that have played in the LIV Golf series will be allowed to compete at the Masters next year, organizers of the prestigious major said on Tuesday.

TITLE: Taliban suspend university education for women in Afghanistan
SUMMARY: The Taliban government has suspended university education for all female students in Afghanistan, the latest step in its brutal clampdown on the rights and freedoms of Afghan women.

TITLE: After Twitter users voted to oust Elon Musk as CEO, he wants to change how polls work
SUMMARY: When Elon Musk polled Twitter users about whether to reinstate former President Donald Trump's account, he quickly followed through on the majority's wish to do so. "Vox Populi, Vox Dei," he pronounced via tweet, Latin for "the voice of the people is the voice of God."

TITLE: What should I do if my flight has been canceled or delayed?
SUMMARY: Here are some expert tips about what travelers should do when flights are delayed or canceled.

TITLE: Tens of thousands without power after 6.4 magnitude earthquake strikes Northern California
SUMMARY: A 6.4 magnitude earthquake struck Northern California's Eureka area early Tuesday, the US Geological Survey said, injuring at least two people, drawing reports of  damage to roads and homes, shaking residents from their sleep and leaving tens of thousands without electricity.

TITLE: Don't send Grandma to the ICU this Christmas
SUMMARY: People are coughing and sneezing -- unmasked -- in public places and transportation this holiday season. This disregard for taking simple steps to stay well and stop the spread of viruses that are at disruptive at best and deadly at worst. We should do better.

TITLE: Here's what's in the $1.7 trillion federal spending bill
SUMMARY: Senate leaders unveiled a $1.7 trillion year-long federal government funding bill early Tuesday morning.

TITLE: Families left in limbo at US border as Trump-era border policy remains in place
SUMMARY: Nine-year-old Rubi Mota can't remember the last time she was in a classroom.

TITLE: First on CNN: Treasury Department to roll out new policy to make global humanitarian support easier
SUMMARY: With humanitarian and food crises growing more dire around the world, the Biden administration plans to roll out new steps on Tuesday to make it easier for humanitarian assistance to continue flowing without concerns about US sanctions, according to senior Treasury officials.

TITLE: Polar air and a powerful winter storm put millions under winter alerts this holiday week
SUMMARY: For millions of Americans across a large swath of the country, the holiday week is beginning with unrelenting below-freezing temperatures made even more miserable by heavy snow expected Tuesday and Wednesday in several central and northwestern states.

TITLE: First images of British banknotes featuring King Charles III unveiled
SUMMARY: The first images of banknotes featuring Britain's King Charles III were unveiled on Tuesday by the Bank of England.

TITLE: 3M will stop making hazardous 'forever chemicals' starting in 2025
SUMMARY: 3M, the conglomerate behind Post-It notes and Scotch tape, will stop making controversial per- and polyfluoroalkyl substances (PFAS) by the end of 2025.

TITLE: Jerry Bruckheimer would 'love' to have Johnny Depp back in 'Pirates' franchise
SUMMARY: Jerry Bruckheimer sounds like he would like to work with Johnny Depp again.

TITLE: Wells Fargo ordered to pay $3.7 billion for 'illegal activity' including unjust foreclosures and vehicle repossessions
SUMMARY: Federal regulators fined Wells Fargo a record $1.7 billion on Tuesday for "widespread mismanagement" over multiple years that harmed over 16 million consumer accounts.

TITLE: World Cup champion Argentina returns home to a jubilant Buenos Aires
SUMMARY: Argentina's World Cup-winning squad arrived home to a jubilant Buenos Aires in the early hours of Tuesday morning, with massive crowds lining the streets and cheering their champions' return.

TITLE: Sharon Osbourne says she's 'doing great' after medical emergency
SUMMARY: Sharon Osbourne has shared an update on her health after a recent hospital visit.

TITLE: EPA finalizes tougher pollution standards for large vehicles like trucks and buses
SUMMARY: The Biden administration on Tuesday finalized tougher pollution standards for heavy-duty vehicles like large trucks, delivery vans and buses starting with model year 2027.

TITLE: 3 suicides in 1 week on same aircraft carrier were unrelated, Navy investigation finds
SUMMARY: A US Navy investigation found that three suicides within one week in April among the crew of an aircraft carrier in Newport News, Virginia, were "not related or connected."

TITLE: Man arrested for allegedly vandalizing menorah with a Nazi symbol in California
SUMMARY: A man was arrested after he allegedly vandalized a menorah in California and carved a Nazi symbol into its base, the Beverly Hills Police Department said in a news release.

TITLE: Opinion: The January 6 committee's devastating conclusions
SUMMARY: Julian Zelizer questions what impact the January 6 committee's devastating findings will have in today's chaotic political environment. He suggests the final report may become ancient history, barring successful prosecutions of key players.

TITLE: EU accepts Amazon commitments in antitrust agreement affecting data and sellers
SUMMARY: The European Union has struck a deal with Amazon that will resolve multiple antitrust investigations into the company and impose binding restrictions on the e-commerce giant's business, in another major step by EU officials to rein in Big Tech.
